name: Jervell and Lange-Nielsen syndrome
ghr-page: https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/condition/jervell-and-lange-nielsen-syndrome
text/text-role: description
text/html/html:p: Jervell and Lange-Nielsen syndrome is a condition that causes profound hearing loss from birth and a disruption of the heart's normal rhythm (arrhythmia).  This disorder is a form of long QT syndrome, which is a heart condition that causes the heart (cardiac) muscle to take longer than usual to recharge between beats.  Beginning in early childhood, the irregular heartbeats increase the risk of fainting (syncope) and sudden death.
inheritance-pattern/code: ar
inheritance-pattern/memo: autosomal recessive
related-gene(1)/gene-symbol: KCNE1
related-gene(1)/ghr-page: https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/gene/KCNE1
related-gene(2)/gene-symbol: KCNQ1
related-gene(2)/ghr-page: https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/gene/KCNQ1
synonym(1): autosomal recessive long QT syndrome (LQTS)
synonym(2): cardio-auditory-syncope syndrome
synonym(3): cardioauditory syndrome of Jervell and Lange-Nielsen
synonym(4): deafness, congenital, and functional heart disease
synonym(5): Jervell-Lange Nielsen syndrome
synonym(6): JLNS
synonym(7): prolonged QT interval in EKG and sudden death
synonym(8): surdo-cardiac syndrome
